posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
Please share the versions of software libraries (In VSCode, click the WPILib icon or Ctrl+Shift+P to open the command palette and run the “WPILib: Open Project Information” command and paste the results here), as well as the firmware version of your SparkMax controllers.

I suspect something is outdated and needs to be updated.

posts.name: Joe
posts.cooked:
Hey OP,

Check this thread: https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/ids-8-received-parameter-invalid-error-parameter-id-113/481477/6

We’re currently working through getting swerve working with YAGSL as well. For this specific error, I see that you have the example json configuration from the YAGSL github. You’ll have to update the physicalproperties.json conversionFactor to the new “conversionFactors” which has additional data. See below for an example:

link_counts.title: IDs: 8, Received parameter invalid error parameter id 113

posts.name: Cody B.
posts.cooked:
apologies for the slow response.

I noticed in your actual Module JSON files you are using “type”: “sparkmax” try swapping those to “type”: “sparkmax_neo”

and see if that fixes anything. It looks like your main issue is with the SparkMax motor controllers, specifically in relation to the swervelib. Those JSON files should really be the only place that you are manually referencing them, and the rest is handled by the YAGSL library.

posts.name: Owen Perez
posts.cooked: Thank you! I figured out I had the filesystem messed up as it was trying to reference the velocity conversion factor.

posts.name: Owen Perez
posts.cooked: I did not notice that, thanks!
